# Set Git's default behaviour to text-files autodetection, in case users don't
# have `core.autocrlf` set:

* text=auto

# ==============================================================================
#                    Text Files (EOL Normalization Settings)                    
# ==============================================================================
# Explicitly declare all files that are text and tell Git how to handle EOLs:

## ================
## PolyGen Grammars
## ================
*.grm          text

## ===========================
## Highlight langDefs & Themes
## ===========================
*.lang         text
*.theme        text

## ================
## Shell scripts
## ================
*.bat          text eol=crlf
*.com          text eol=crlf
*.sh           text eol=lf

## ================
## Documents files
## ================
*.htm          text
*.html         text
*.markdown     text
*.md           text

## =================
## PP macros modules
## =================
*.pp           text

## ================
## Documentation
## ================
LICENSE        text

## ================
## Git settings
## ================
.gitattributes text
.gitconfig     text
.gitignore     text
.gitmodules    text

# ==============================================================================
#                                  Binary Files                                 
# ==============================================================================
# Explicitly declare all files that are binary and shouldn't be modified by Git:

## =========================
## PolyGen Compiled Grammars
## =========================
*.grm.o      binary


## ================
## Windows Binaries
## ================
*.exe        binary

# ==============================================================================
#                                GitHub Linguist                                
# ==============================================================================
#  -- https://github.com/github/linguist
#
# Manually define/override some extension so that GitHub's Linguist library can
# 1) Correctly gather statistics on source files, and
# 2) Use proper syntax highlighting on GitHub's WebUI.

## ============================
## PolyGen Grammars (sources)
## ============================
*.grm    linguist-language=EBNF

## ===========================
## Highlight langDefs & Themes
## ===========================
*.lang   linguist-language=Lua
*.theme  linguist-language=Lua